The paper deals with mechanism design for combinatorial cost sharing, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses parameterizations of cost functions and social cost approximation, which are topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and economics (cs.EC). The use of iterative mechanisms and group-strategyproofness also suggests a connection to learning theory (cs.LG).
